## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="c0a7a-139">次の例では、語句を認識する文法「ワールド カップが勝利した民族が」とそれに続くワールド カップが勝利した国の名前。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c0a7a-139">The following example creates a grammar that recognizes the phrase "A nation that has won the World Cup is" followed by the name of a country that has won the World Cup.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c0a7a-140">例では、という名前のパブリック ルールを作成する`WorldCupWinner`です。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c0a7a-140">The example creates a public rule named `WorldCupWinner`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c0a7a-141">例では、2 つ作成し<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule>オブジェクト、`ruleEurope`と`ruleSAmerica`を渡して、<xref:System.String>ルールの識別子と<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsElement>配列を含む、<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf>オブジェクト。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c0a7a-141">The example then creates two <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> objects, `ruleEurope` and  `ruleSAmerica`, passing in a <xref:System.String> for the rule identifier and an <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsElement> array containing a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> object.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c0a7a-142">例では、によってルール参照が追加、その後、`ruleEurope`と`ruleSAmerica`ルールから`WorldCupWinner`です。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c0a7a-142">Subsequently, the example adds rule references to `ruleEurope` and `ruleSAmerica` from the rule `WorldCupWinner`.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
public void WorldSoccerWinners ()  
{  
  // Create a grammar from an SRGSDocument, create a new rule  
  // and set its scope to public.  
  SrgsDocument srgsGrammar = new SrgsDocument ();  
  SrgsRule winnerRule = new SrgsRule ("WorldCupWinner");  
  winnerRule.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
  // Add the introduction.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add (new SrgsItem ("A nation that has won the world cup is"));  
  
  // Create the rule for the European nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfEurope = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("England"), new SrgsItem("France"), new SrgsItem("Germany"), new SrgsItem("Italy")});  
  SrgsRule ruleEurope = (new SrgsRule("EuropeanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfEurope}));  
  
  // Create the rule for the South American nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfSAmerica = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("Argentina"), new SrgsItem("Brazil"), new SrgsItem("Uruguay")});  
  SrgsRule ruleSAmerica = (new SrgsRule("SouthAmericanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfSAmerica}));  
  
  // Add references to winnerRule for ruleEurope and ruleSAmerica.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {(new SrgsItem (new SrgsRuleRef(ruleEurope))), new SrgsItem(new SrgsRuleRef(ruleSAmerica))}));  
  
  // Add all the rules to the grammar and make winnerRule  
  // the root rule of the grammar.  
  document.Rules.Add(new SrgsRule[] {winnerRule, ruleEurope, ruleSAmerica});  
  srgsGrammar.Root = winnerRule;  
}  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="c0a7a-143">作成された文法には、次の形式があります。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c0a7a-143">The created grammar has the following form.</span></span>  
  
```xml  
<grammar version="1.0" xml:lang="en-US" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2001/06/grammar" root="WorldCupWinner">  
    <rule id="WorldCupWinner" scope="public">  
        <item> A nation that has won the world cup is </item>  
        <one-of>  
            <item>  
                <ruleref uri="#EuropeanNations" />  
            </item>  
            <item>  
                <ruleref uri="#SouthAmericanNations" />  
            </item>  
        </one-of>  
    </rule>  
    <rule id="EuropeanNations">  
        <one-of>  
            <item> England </item>  
            <item> France </item>  
            <item> Germany </item>  
            <item> Italy </item>  
        </one-of>  
    </rule>  
    <rule id="SouthAmericanNations">  
        <one-of>  
            <item> Argentina </item>  
            <item> Brazil </item>  
            <item> Uruguay </item>  
        </one-of>  
    </rule>  
</grammar>  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="c0a7a-150">一般的な追加機能が、<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule>オブジェクトが含まれます<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem>、 <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf>、 <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef>、および<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken>言えるスピーカーを指定するオブジェクト。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c0a7a-150">Typical additions to an <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> object include <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem>, <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf>, <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef>, and <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken> objects that specify what speakers can say.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c0a7a-151">有効なルール要素には、少なくとも 2 つの認識可能なテキストまたは 1 つのルール参照を含める必要があります。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c0a7a-151">A valid rule element must contain at least one piece of recognizable text or one rule reference.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c0a7a-152">参照してください[文法を使用して SrgsGrammar の作成](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/e4d9f96e-2241-4c39-b9e0-ac9ef4e9a906)詳細についてはします。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c0a7a-152">See [Create Grammars Using SrgsGrammar](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/e4d9f96e-2241-4c39-b9e0-ac9ef4e9a906) for more information.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="c0a7a-153"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule>オブジェクトが含まれることも<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsNameValueTag>と<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag>セマンティック値、およびセマンティック キー、ルールを追加するオブジェクト。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c0a7a-153">An <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> object may also contain <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsNameValueTag> and <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag> objects that add semantic values and semantic keys to the rule.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c0a7a-154">音声認識エンジンには、という語句を認識すると認識された語句と同様に、セマンティック情報が返すされます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c0a7a-154">The speech recognition engine will return the semantic information, as well as the recognized phrase, when it recognizes the phrase.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c0a7a-155">参照してください[セマンティクス解釈マークアップ](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/2e115391-73b3-4666-8fd1-540c529de3b0)詳細についてはします。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c0a7a-155">See [Semantic Interpretation Markup](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/2e115391-73b3-4666-8fd1-540c529de3b0) for more information.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="c0a7a-156">次の例では、語句を認識する文法「ワールド カップが勝利した民族が」とそれに続くワールド カップが勝利した国の名前。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c0a7a-156">The following example creates a grammar that recognizes the phrase "A nation that has won the World Cup is" followed by the name of a country that has won the World Cup.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c0a7a-157">作成した後、<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule>オブジェクト`winnerRule`文字列識別子を与えると`WorldCupWinner`、この例では、<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Add%2A>文字列を追加する方法のルールに「ワールド カップが勝利した民族は」。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c0a7a-157">After creating the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> object `winnerRule` and giving it the string identifier `WorldCupWinner`, the example uses the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Add%2A> method to append the string  "A nation that has won the World Cup is" to the rule.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c0a7a-158">追加の 2 つの規則を作成し`ruleEurope`と`ruleSAmerica`です。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c0a7a-158">The example then creates two additional rules, `ruleEurope` and  `ruleSAmerica`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c0a7a-159">使ってもう一度、<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Add%2A>メソッド、例では、追加、<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf>オブジェクトを`WorldCupWinner`にルール参照が含まれるルール`ruleEurope`と`ruleSAmerica`です。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c0a7a-159">Again using the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Add%2A> method, the example appends an <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> object to the `WorldCupWinner` rule that contains rule references to `ruleEurope` and `ruleSAmerica`.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
// Create an SrgsDocument, create a new rule  
// and set its scope to public.  
SrgsDocument document = new SrgsDocument();  
SrgsRule winnerRule = new SrgsRule("WorldCupWinner");  
winnerRule.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
// Add the introduction.  
winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsItem("A nation that has won the world cup is: "));  
  
// Create the rule for the European nations.  
SrgsOneOf oneOfEurope = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("England"), new SrgsItem("France"), new SrgsItem("Germany"), new SrgsItem("Italy")});  
SrgsRule ruleEurope = (new SrgsRule("EuropeanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfEurope}));  
  
// Create the rule for the South American nations.  
SrgsOneOf oneOfSAmerica = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("Argentina"), new SrgsItem("Brazil"), new SrgsItem("Uruguay")});  
SrgsRule ruleSAmerica = (new SrgsRule("SouthAmericanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfSAmerica}));  
  
// Add references to winnerRule for ruleEurope and ruleSAmerica.  
winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {(new SrgsItem (new SrgsRuleRef(ruleEurope))), new SrgsItem(new SrgsRuleRef(ruleSAmerica))}));  
  
// Add all the rules to the document and make winnerRule   
// the root rule of the document.  
document.Rules.Add(new SrgsRule[] {winnerRule, ruleEurope, ruleSAmerica});  
document.Root = winnerRule;  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="c0a7a-186">スコープの既定値は`Private`します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c0a7a-186">The default value for scope is `Private`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c0a7a-187">プライベート ルールは、そのを含む文法にルート ルールまたはルート ルールから参照されている別のルールからのルール参照によって認識用のみアクティブにできます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c0a7a-187">A private rule can only be activated for recognition by a rule reference from the root rule in its containing grammar or from another rule that is referenced from the root rule.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c0a7a-188">プライベートのルールはそのを含む文法のルート ルールとして宣言されていない限り、プライベート ルールは、外部の文法で参照できません。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c0a7a-188">A private rule cannot be referenced by an external grammar, unless the private rule is declared as the root rule of its containing grammar.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="c0a7a-189">そのスコープが設定されている場合`Public`、<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule>から参照渡しで認識に対してオブジェクトをアクティブ化でき、<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef>を含む文法または外部の文法でルールからのオブジェクト。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c0a7a-189">If its scope is set to `Public`, an <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> object can be activated for recognition by a reference from a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef> object in the containing grammar or from a rule in an external grammar.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="c0a7a-190">次の例では、語句を認識する文法「ワールド カップが勝利した民族が」とそれに続くワールド カップが勝利した国の名前。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c0a7a-190">The following example creates a grammar that recognizes the phrase "A nation that has won the World Cup is" followed by the name of a country that has won the World Cup.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c0a7a-191">という名前のパブリック規則が作成`WorldCupWinner`し、そのルールのスコープをパブリックに設定します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c0a7a-191">It creates a public rule named `WorldCupWinner` and sets the scope of that rule to Public.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
// Create an SrgsDocument, create a new rule and set its scope to public.  
SrgsDocument document = new SrgsDocument();  
SrgsRule winnerRule = new SrgsRule("WorldCupWinner");  
winnerRule.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
// Add the introduction.  
winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsItem("A nation that has won the world cup is: "));  
  
// Create the rule for the European nations.  
SrgsOneOf oneOfEurope = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("England"), new SrgsItem("France"), new SrgsItem("Germany"), new SrgsItem("Italy")});  
SrgsRule ruleEurope = (new SrgsRule("EuropeanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfEurope}));  
  
// Create the rule for the South American nations.  
SrgsOneOf oneOfSAmerica = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("Argentina"), new SrgsItem("Brazil"), new SrgsItem("Uruguay")});  
SrgsRule ruleSAmerica = (new SrgsRule("SouthAmericanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfSAmerica}));  
  
// Add references to winnerRule for ruleEurope and ruleSAmerica.  
winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {(new SrgsItem (new SrgsRuleRef(ruleEurope)), new SrgsItem(new SrgsRuleRef(ruleSAmerica)})));  
  
// Add all the rules to the document and make winnerRule   
// the root rule of the document.  
document.Rules.Add(new SrgsRule[] {winnerRule, ruleEurope, ruleSAmerica});  
document.Root = winnerRule;  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="c0a7a-192">作成された文法には、次の形式があります。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c0a7a-192">The created grammar has the following form.</span></span>  
  
```xml  
<grammar version="1.0" xml:lang="en-US" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2001/06/grammar" root="WorldCupWinner">  
    <rule id="WorldCupWinner" scope="public">  
        <item> A nation that has won the world cup is </item>  
        <one-of>  
            <item>  
                <ruleref uri="#EuropeanNations" />  
            </item>  
            <item>  
                <ruleref uri="#SouthAmericanNations" />  
            </item>  
        </one-of>  
    </rule>  
    <rule id="EuropeanNations">  
        <one-of>  
            <item> England< /item>  
            <item> France </item>  
            <item> Germany </item>  
            <item> Italy </item>  
        </one-of>  
    </rule>  
    <rule id="SouthAmericanNations">  
        <one-of>  
            <item> Argentina </item>  
            <item> Brazil </item>  
            <item> Uruguay </item>  
        </one-of>  
    </rule>  
</grammar>  
```
